<item>
            <title>[LU-9739] sanity-quota test_18: mount: can&apos;t find /mnt/lustre-mds in /etc/fstab</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9739</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah_lw &amp;lt;wei3.liu@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/9dd6b862-61c1-11e7-8a1d-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/9dd6b862-61c1-11e7-8a1d-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_18 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Restart of mds failed!

Failover mds to onyx-69
20:41:21 (1499028081) waiting for onyx-69 network 900 secs ...
20:41:21 (1499028081) network interface is UP
mount facets: mds
onyx-69: Usage: e2label device [newlabel]
Starting mds:    /mnt/lustre-mds
onyx-69: mount: can&apos;t find /mnt/lustre-mds in /etc/fstab
Start of  on mds failed 1
 sanity-quota test_18: @@@@@@ FAIL: Restart of mds failed! 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test steps:&lt;br/&gt;
1. format and setup system with 2.9.0&lt;br/&gt;
2. make files and set u/g quota&lt;br/&gt;
3. stop and upgrade system to 2.10.0&lt;br/&gt;
4. verify u/g quota works, add a new OST and enable project quota and verify it works&lt;br/&gt;
5. stop and disable project quota, downgrade the system(with new added OST) to 2.9.0&lt;br/&gt;
6. run sanity-quota and hit the problem&lt;/p&gt;</description>
